parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Forward Collision Warning and Traction Control System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the forward collision warning and traction control system can lead to accidents, as the vehicle may not respond properly to emergency braking situations.
symptoms: The forward collision warning and traction control lights are stuck on
the Automatic Emergency Braking (AEB) System Warning Light and the Slip Indicator Light come on intermittently
the start button may not work
and the vehicle may shut off or not shift out of park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood latch system can cause the hood to shake or come loose while driving, which can lead to accidents or obstruct the driver's view.
symptoms: The hood shakes or bounces even when locked
the hood may not close properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Sensor and Radar Obstruction Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front sensor and radar system can cause false alerts and unnecessary braking, which can lead to accidents or disrupt the driver's control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The front sensor shows "unavailable" or "obstruction" alerts
the vehicle may brake unnecessarily
the system may malfunction even when there are no obstacles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: These issues can cause safety risks, discomfort, and inconvenience to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Metal rattling noise from under the car
airbag failure to deploy in an accident
touch screen panel and radio freezing
transmission issues
and rough driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Loss of Power and Acceleration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power and acceleration can cause the vehicle to stall or slow down unexpectedly, increasing the risk of accidents, especially in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops accelerating
takes a long time to reach a certain speed
or stalls while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Collision Sensor and Radar System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front collision sensor and radar system can cause the vehicle's safety features, such as cruise control and collision avoidance braking, to malfunction or shut off, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The front collision sensor light illuminates
the breaking system light illuminates
the cruise control shuts off
the collision avoidance braking system is disabled
the vehicle stalls or loses power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: ABS Light and Brake Fluid Leak
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ABS light coming on and staying on can indicate a brake fluid leak, which can cause a fire hazard and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS light comes on and stays on
the vehicle loses power or stalls while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sluggish or malfunctioning cruise control can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control is slow to engage
the cruise control disengages unexpectedly
the vehicle suddenly accelerates without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down while driving, leading to potential accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle randomly turns off and turns back on
the dashboard lights turn off and back on
the speakers make a loud BOOM sound
the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the infotainment system can cause the backup camera to malfunction, increasing the risk of accidents or damage to the vehicle, person, or property.
symptoms: The display screen does not work
the stereo loops or freezes
the backup camera may not display an image or may display an image for only a short time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window and lighting systems can cause inconvenience and reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windows may not roll up or down properly
the back lights may not work at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the braking system can cause accidents or injuries, especially if the vehicle is unable to stop in time.
symptoms: The brakes may fail without warning
the brake pedal may go to the floor
the ABS light may be illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission defect can cause the vehicle to slip or jerk, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The transmission may slip or jerk
the vehicle may shake violently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the collision detection radar system can cause the automated braking system and adaptive cruise control to malfunction, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The warning light comes on
the radar sensor may need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the keyless entry system can cause inconvenience and potentially strand the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle may automatically lock with the keys inside
the vehicle may not unlock.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trunk and radio systems can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The trunk may not open properly
the radio may randomly delete stations or black out with navigation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The contamination of the stop lamp switch can cause the car to not start, not able to switch gears, and the brake light to not turn on, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The car won't start
unable to switch gears
brake light not turning on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent appearance of ABS warning lights can cause confusion and distraction for the driver, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: ABS warning light
traction control warning light
and emergency brake warning light intermittently come on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The incomplete repair of the ABS actuator can cause the ABS warning lights to continue to appear, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: ABS warning lights continue to appear after repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall repair parts can cause delays in repairing safety issues, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Part to do the recall repair was unavailable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty front radar sensor can cause the emergency braking system to malfunction, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Warning flashes on the dashboard indicating "Front Radar Unavailable"
frequent deactivation of the radar sensor
disabling cruise control and emergency braking system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly hesitates or loses power
the transmission slips or feels like it's in neutral
the vehicle may shake or vibrate
and there may be unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the 4x4 system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially in snowy or slippery conditions.
symptoms: The 4x4 system fails to engage or disengages unexpectedly
the vehicle slides or loses traction
and the driver may experience difficulty controlling the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unexpected airbag deployment can cause accidents or injuries, and may also lead to a loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The airbags deploy unexpectedly
the vehicle may shake or vibrate
and there may be a loud explosion or noise.
